<title>FRANCE: Skis Rossignol 96/97 net profit drops.</title>
<headline>Skis Rossignol 96/97 net profit drops.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-06-17</dateline>
<text>
<p>Year to March 31, 1997.</p>
<p>(Figures in millions of French francs unless stated)</p>
<p>    Net					     76.1  vs	   115.7</p>
<p>    Operating				    203.4  vs	   212.3</p>
<p>    Investments				  188.1  vs	   150.9</p>
<p>    Cashflow				     232.1  vs	   243.5</p>
<p>    Turnover				   2,367.7  vs	 2,122.1</p>
<p>    Dividend net (francs)			2.50 vs	see note</p>
<p>NOTE - The group said in its results statement the dividend after adjustment was equivelent to that of last year's payout when it paid 30 francs per share. A spokeswoman said the group had issued two free shares for every share last October and divided the nominal share value by four.</p>
<p>The group said the net result drop profit was due in part to a negative financial result to the tune of 19.3 million francs, exceptional provisions of 10.5 million and a write-down of 3.5 million francs.</p>
<p>-- Paris Newsroom +33 1 4221 5452</p>
